data.chText: 受煎熬的；患病的；遭受挫折的
data.enText: seriously affected by an unpleasant feeling or disease or by a difficult situation

data.chText: 她仰起苦闷的脸，乞求帮助。
data.enText: She raised her stricken face and begged for help.

data.chText: 整村整村的人染上了这种病。
data.enText: Whole villages were stricken with the disease.

data.chText: 他在五十岁生日那天心脏病发作。
data.enText: He was stricken by a heart attack on his fiftieth birthday.

data.chText: 我们前去救助那艘失事的船。
data.enText: We went to the aid of the stricken boat.
seriously affected by the thing mentioned

tr: (used in combination) affected by something overwhelming

value.def: Stricken is the past participle of some meanings of strike .
If a person or place is stricken by something such as an unpleasant feeling, an illness, or a natural disaster, they are severely affected by it.

example.ex: ...a family stricken by genetically inherited cancer...
example.tran: 受遗传性癌症折磨的一家

example.ex: Foreign aid workers will not be allowed into the stricken areas.
example.tran: 国外救援人员不准进入灾区。

example.ex: He was panic-stricken at the thought he might never play again.
example.tran: 一想到自己可能永远不能再参加比赛，他就无比恐慌。

value.tran: 受煎熬的;患病的;遭受挫折的;受灾的
